The 2019 MyBroadband Conference and Expo has kicked off at the Gallagher Convention Centre in Midrand. The annual MyBroadband Conference is the premier ICT event in South Africa and the meeting place for the country’s IT and telecoms community. Speakers at the conference include MTN SA CEO Godfrey Motsa, Liquid Telecom CEO Reshaad Sha, and former Telkom COO Brian Armstrong. Delegates will also hear from SqwidNet MD Phathizwe Malinga, Vodacom chief officer Jorge Mendes, and Q-KON Africa CEO Dawie de Wet. The conference will feature two international speakers – Bell Labs’ Fuad Siddiqui and Huawei Carrier Business Group’s Nigel Bruin. There will also be a panel discussion chaired by Jan Vermeulen, which will feature Supersonic MD Calvin Collett, Vodacom’s executive head for innovation Jannie van Zyl, and Huawei South Africa CTO Akhram Mohamed. You can watch the conference live, below, thanks to our streaming partner Antfarm. <span data-mce-type="bookmark" style="display: inline-block; width: 0px; overflow: hidden; line-height: 0;" class="mce_SELRES_start">﻿</span>